  "text": "14 Bacterial density Piperacillin/tazobactam: for the lower initial bacterial density, trough total plasma piperacillin concentration/MIC ratios of 3.4 and 10.4 following bolus and extended-infusion regimens, respectively, were able to suppress the emergence of piperacillin resistance. For the higher initial bacterial density, both infusion regimens were associated with progressive growth of a resistant subpopulation, and thus combination therapy may be required to maximize bacterial killing and prevent antimicrobial resistance. [CITATION_1] Total daily dose Imipenem/cilastatin: In critically ill patients with nosocomial pneumonia, concentrations of imipenem were above the target concentration (4×MIC of 2 mg/L) for ≥40% of the dosing interval in every patient in the bolus group (1 g imipenem/1 g cilastatin over 30 minutes every 8 hours), whereas in the extended group (0.5 g of imipenem by a 3-hour infusion every 6 hours) this PK/ PD index (40% fT>4×MIC) was achieved in only 20% of patients. Moreover, 70% of the patients in the extended group did not reach the desired drug concentrations at all. [CITATION_2] ",
