      "span_text": "For the higher initial bacterial density, both infusion regimens were associated with progressive growth of a resistant subpopulation, and thus combination therapy may be required to maximize bacterial killing and prevent antimicrobial resistance. Total daily dose Imipenem/cilastatin: In critically ill patients with nosocomial pneumonia, concentrations of imipenem were above the target concentration (4×MIC of 2 mg/L) for ≥40% of the dosing interval in every patient in the bolus group (1 g imipenem/1 g cilastatin over 30 minutes every 8 hours), whereas in the extended group (0.5 g of imipenem by a 3-hour infusion every 6 hours) this PK/ PD index (40% fT>4×MIC) was achieved in only 20% of patients."
